cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CE, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of bibliometric indicators for the evaluation of individual researchers, which is a common topic in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), computational science (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer engineering (cs.CE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). While the paper does not focus on a specific subfield, it touches on aspects that are relevant to all of these areas.
